flowRoot.flowPara: GANs are able to create synthetic images by learning data distributions. Radford et al. 2016 proposed Deep Convolutional GANs (DCGANs) to improve image quality generation and training stability of the networks with the use of stride CNNs, extensive use of batchNorm [5].
We make use of an open dataset of 999 real fetal head US images [6]. Fetal US images are from all trimesters with a pixel size of width 800 x height 540.
